value.name: North Korean satellite launch could be major provocation if successful
value.description: The botched attempt triggered emergency alerts in Seoul and on the southern Japanese island of Okinawa. Ellen Kim, the deputy director of the Korea Chair at the Center for Strategic and International Studies, joined CBS News to talk about the failed launch.
